1
00:00:39,567 --> 00:00:42,033
<i>- Mom!
- Coleen, let's go.</i>

2
00:00:42,167 --> 00:00:45,333
<i>Dad wants to go to
Miss Hazel, Mom.</i>

3
00:00:45,467 --> 00:00:46,933
<i> Oh, no! You can't do that.</i>

4
00:00:47,067 --> 00:00:49,000
<i> Our children are outside!</i>

5
00:00:49,133 --> 00:00:50,033
<i> Our children?</i>

6
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:53,467
<i> I'll go find them...</i>

7
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:54,267
<i> Where are you going?</i>

8
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:55,833
<i> I'll look for Mom and Coleen.</i>

9
00:00:55,967 --> 00:00:57,933
<i>I'll find out what
they're keeping from us.</i>

10
00:00:58,067 --> 00:00:59,333
<i> No, go have some dessert...</i>

11
00:00:59,467 --> 00:01:00,467
<i> Oh, my!</i>

12
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:01,600
<i> You did it on purpose</i>

13
00:01:01,733 --> 00:01:03,567
<i>because you're in cahoots
with Coleen and Mom!</i>

14
00:01:03,700 --> 00:01:05,233
<i> Andrea, that's enough.</i>

15
00:01:05,367 --> 00:01:07,033
<i> Jessica is calling.</i>

16
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:08,400
<i> Yes, Dad. I'm here already.</i>

17
00:01:08,533 --> 00:01:11,833
<i>I'm hiding right now
because Jeffrey is here.</i>

18
00:01:15,433 --> 00:01:16,567
<i> Hey!</i>

19
00:01:16,700 --> 00:01:17,967
<i>Your classmate has been waiting
outside for a while now.</i>

20
00:01:18,100 --> 00:01:19,967
<i>- Who is she?
- She's my classmate.</i>

21
00:01:20,100 --> 00:01:20,900
<i> Her name is Jane.</i>

22
00:01:21,033 --> 00:01:22,533
<i> Nice meeting you.</i>

23
00:01:22,667 --> 00:01:24,033
<i> Your voice sounds familiar.</i>

24
00:01:26,567 --> 00:01:27,967
<i>- There's an intruder!
- Hey!</i>

25
00:01:28,100 --> 00:01:31,133
<i> Don't! Don't! Son, son, son!</i>

26
00:01:31,267 --> 00:01:32,367
<i>Get out of here!
Son, that's enough!</i>

27
00:01:32,500 --> 00:01:33,733
<i> Son, stop!</i>

28
00:01:33,867 --> 00:01:36,200
<i>You've got some nerve showing
your face after you screwed up!</i>

29
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:37,533
<i> But I got away, didn't I?</i>

30
00:01:37,667 --> 00:01:38,933
<i>Your husband and kid
weren't there.</i>

31
00:01:39,067 --> 00:01:41,000
<i>There wasn't anyone with them
in a wheelchair anyway.</i>

32
00:01:41,167 --> 00:01:42,567
<i> Oh my!</i>

33
00:01:42,700 --> 00:01:44,500
<i> I'm back to square one.</i>

34
00:01:58,333 --> 00:01:59,300
What's wrong with you?

35
00:01:59,433 --> 00:02:01,267
It's so early, and you're
already pestering me,

36
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,767
you, goblin!

37
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:04,100
What do you want?

38
00:02:04,233 --> 00:02:05,333
You're such a nuisance!

39
00:02:05,467 --> 00:02:06,400
<i> Hey!</i>

40
00:02:06,533 --> 00:02:09,267
Turn on your video!

41
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:11,067
Learn some etiquette, will you?

42
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:13,200
<i> Wow!</i>

43
00:02:13,333 --> 00:02:15,533
Oh, listen to you talking
about basic etiquette.

44
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:18,267
As if anyone would ever
give you a certificate

45
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:20,167
for good manners
and right conduct!

46
00:02:20,300 --> 00:02:21,500
Video call?

47
00:02:21,633 --> 00:02:22,700
Fine!

48
00:02:22,833 --> 00:02:24,167
<i>- Video call your own face!
- What even is that?</i>

49
00:02:24,300 --> 00:02:25,800
<i>Why is it focused
on the trash can?</i>

50
00:02:25,933 --> 00:02:28,667
See? It's like you're looking
in a mirror!

51
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:29,833
<i> You look awful!</i>

52
00:02:29,967 --> 00:02:32,633
You're seriously crazy,
you know that?

53
00:02:32,767 --> 00:02:33,200
<i> Really?</i>

54
00:02:33,333 --> 00:02:34,500
I'm the crazy one?

55
00:02:34,633 --> 00:02:37,667
Why are you even bothering me?

56
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:39,067
<i> Help me.</i>

57
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:43,167
Help me find Manuel
and Jessica that Felma hid.

58
00:02:43,300 --> 00:02:45,367
<i> Wow! Feeling close?</i>

59
00:02:45,500 --> 00:02:47,500
<i>You think my help
for you is unlimited?</i>

60
00:02:47,667 --> 00:02:48,433
<i> No, girl!</i>

61
00:02:48,567 --> 00:02:50,300
That was a one-time,
big-time deal.

62
00:02:50,433 --> 00:02:51,800
You don't have a choice.

63
00:02:51,933 --> 00:02:53,333
<i> Are you going to help me?</i>

64
00:02:53,467 --> 00:02:56,200
<i>If you don't, I'll go
straight to Felma's office</i>

65
00:02:56,333 --> 00:02:58,400
and tell her that you were
on it with me.

66
00:02:58,533 --> 00:02:59,667
Is that blackmail?

67
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:00,800
Okay, come on!

68
00:03:00,933 --> 00:03:02,100
Make my day!

69
00:03:02,233 --> 00:03:03,333
Come on down!

70
00:03:03,467 --> 00:03:06,333
I'll have the guards
drag you out!

71
00:03:06,467 --> 00:03:07,333
<i> Don't you dare...</i>

72
00:03:07,467 --> 00:03:08,967
Paz!

73
00:03:09,100 --> 00:03:09,667
This monster
is really rude...

74
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:11,033
So, classmate?

75
00:03:11,167 --> 00:03:12,533
Do you still need my help?

76
00:03:12,667 --> 00:03:13,700
You're still here?

77
00:03:13,833 --> 00:03:14,467
Just leave already!

78
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:15,500
I don't need you!

79
00:03:15,633 --> 00:03:16,667
Go!

80
00:03:21,067 --> 00:03:22,367
I've got another plan.

81
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:49,567
<i>I hope you all can finally
get along, Coleen.</i>

82
00:03:49,700 --> 00:03:52,433
<i>So you can experience
what it's like to have a father.</i>

83
00:03:59,700 --> 00:04:00,767
Sorry.

84
00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:02,833
I'm sorry.

85
00:04:02,967 --> 00:04:04,833
I was just getting my phone.

86
00:04:04,967 --> 00:04:06,000
Sorry to wake you up.

87
00:04:06,133 --> 00:04:07,867
It's okay.

88
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:10,600
Thank you for letting me
borrow it.

89
00:04:10,733 --> 00:04:12,533
Oh, you look like you
didn't get much sleep.

90
00:04:12,667 --> 00:04:14,667
Is my bed uncomfortable?

91
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:15,500
No, not at all.

92
00:04:15,633 --> 00:04:16,333
It's comfortable.

93
00:04:16,467 --> 00:04:17,867
Thanks for that.

94
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:20,700
But these two dearest daughters
of mine are so talkative.

95
00:04:20,833 --> 00:04:22,400
They have so many stories.

96
00:04:22,533 --> 00:04:25,367
I think we only fell
asleep at dawn.

97
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:26,967
Well, what can we do, Dad?

98
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:30,267
A lot happened last night.

99
00:04:30,433 --> 00:04:33,267
First, Andrea and I had a fight.

100
00:04:33,400 --> 00:04:36,333
Second, Jessica really did
escape from Miss Hazel,

101
00:04:36,467 --> 00:04:38,700
but she almost got caught
by Andrea and Jeffrey.

102
00:04:38,833 --> 00:04:42,733
Did we forget
to tell Dad anything?

103
00:04:42,867 --> 00:04:44,367
I think you covered everything.

104
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:46,967
You already told me everything.

105
00:04:47,100 --> 00:04:51,867
You know, we really need to talk
about leaving this place.

106
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:55,300
Your sister and brother
almost caught us so many times.

107
00:04:55,433 --> 00:04:57,467
Next time, we might
not be so lucky.

108
00:04:57,600 --> 00:05:00,033
That's exactly what
we're trying to avoid.

109
00:05:00,167 --> 00:05:02,267
By the way, you'll be having
breakfast

110
00:05:02,433 --> 00:05:03,733
in the dining room, right?

111
00:05:03,867 --> 00:05:05,900
I'll just call you when
the food is ready, okay?

112
00:05:07,633 --> 00:05:08,500
Thanks, Didang.

113
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:11,267
- Didang.
- Yes?

114
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:13,233
Where are Andrea and Jeffrey?

115
00:05:13,367 --> 00:05:16,567
Jeff took Tetay and Daisy home.

116
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:17,933
Andrea came along

117
00:05:18,067 --> 00:05:21,367
because she said she'd stop by
the office.

118
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:22,167
I'll just get things ready.

119
00:05:22,300 --> 00:05:23,333
I'll call you, okay?

120
00:05:27,133 --> 00:05:29,267
Jessica, I'm just
going to the bathroom.

121
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:30,267
We'll go with you, Dad.

122
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:31,233
No, it's fine.

123
00:05:31,367 --> 00:05:32,467
I can manage on my own.

124
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:40,433
I'm just going to open the door.

125
00:05:47,700 --> 00:05:48,567
Hello?

126
00:05:48,700 --> 00:05:50,700
Did you get the money
I sent you, Dad?

127
00:05:53,667 --> 00:05:56,600
That's for you and Mom's
maintenance, okay?

128
00:05:56,733 --> 00:05:59,533
Don't go spending it all
over the place later, Dad.

129
00:05:59,667 --> 00:06:00,433
Didang?

130
00:06:00,567 --> 00:06:01,133
Didang!

131
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:05,133
Sir.

132
00:06:05,267 --> 00:06:06,667
How did you get in?

133
00:06:08,633 --> 00:06:09,767
The door is open.

134
00:06:09,900 --> 00:06:11,367
And so is the gate.

135
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:14,267
Sir Jeff probably left it open.

136
00:06:16,067 --> 00:06:20,300
It's your responsibility
to secure the gate and the door.

137
00:06:20,433 --> 00:06:22,033
You should be double-checking
those.

138
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:25,333
Yes, I will.

139
00:06:25,467 --> 00:06:27,733
Dad, I'll call you again later.

140
00:06:29,700 --> 00:06:32,367
Sir, does Ma'am Felma
know that you're coming?

141
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:34,000
Not yet.

142
00:06:34,133 --> 00:06:35,767
But please tell her I'm here.

143
00:06:38,300 --> 00:06:41,233
All right, sure. I'll just go
upstairs and let her know.

144
00:06:56,333 --> 00:06:57,033
Man, sorry!

145
00:06:57,167 --> 00:06:58,367
My bad.

146
00:06:58,500 --> 00:06:59,400
It's all good.

147
00:06:59,533 --> 00:07:01,567
<i>This is Noah Salvador,
Felma's fiancé.</i>

148
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:03,233
<i>You'd better stop messing
with me and Felma.</i>

149
00:07:03,367 --> 00:07:04,900
<i> We're about to get married.</i>

150
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:14,600
Is anyone there?

151
00:07:17,167 --> 00:07:18,467
What?

152
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:20,067
Noah is here?

153
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:21,067
Yes, Ma'am.

154
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:24,433
And he wants to talk to you.

155
00:07:24,567 --> 00:07:27,533
Why didn't he call or text?

156
00:07:27,667 --> 00:07:30,600
He knows that I don't want
visitors here on Sundays.

157
00:07:30,733 --> 00:07:33,533
It's our family's rest day.

158
00:07:36,033 --> 00:07:38,400
How about Manuel and Jessica?

159
00:07:38,533 --> 00:07:39,833
They are safe.

160
00:07:39,967 --> 00:07:41,967
They're in my room with Coleen.

161
00:07:42,100 --> 00:07:43,300
Okay.

162
00:07:43,433 --> 00:07:44,433
Please excuse me.

163
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:50,500
Coleen, is that you?

164
00:07:57,333 --> 00:07:58,800
Manuel?

165
00:07:58,933 --> 00:07:59,800
Noah?

166
00:08:05,100 --> 00:08:06,067
What are you doing here?

167
00:08:09,567 --> 00:08:10,733
Coleen brought us here.

168
00:08:10,867 --> 00:08:12,067
And you went along with her!

169
00:08:13,667 --> 00:08:16,067
You've got some nerve!

170
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:17,900
Does Felma even know about this?

171
00:08:18,033 --> 00:08:18,700
Yes, she does.

172
00:08:20,733 --> 00:08:22,600
<i>Felma, would you like me
to hire a security guard</i>

173
00:08:22,767 --> 00:08:23,500
<i> to monitor the gate?</i>

174
00:08:23,633 --> 00:08:24,667
<i> Where is your ex?</i>

175
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:25,900
<i> Do you really not know?</i>

176
00:08:26,033 --> 00:08:27,733
<i> Why would I even hide Manuel?</i>

177
00:08:27,867 --> 00:08:29,400
<i>But Hazel wouldn't have
stormed in like that</i>

178
00:08:29,533 --> 00:08:32,867
<i>- if you didn't know something.
- I don't know where Manuel is!</i>

179
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:36,200
<i>And I am definitely
not hiding him!</i>

180
00:08:38,433 --> 00:08:39,400
Get out!

181
00:08:39,533 --> 00:08:40,400
You have no place here anymore!

182
00:08:40,533 --> 00:08:50,500
You have no place here anymore!

183
00:08:50,633 --> 00:08:53,333
I already told you before!
Don't show yourself to Felma!

184
00:08:53,467 --> 00:08:54,400
Don't you dare show
yourself to Felma!

185
00:08:54,567 --> 00:08:55,533
You have no place here anymore!

186
00:08:55,667 --> 00:08:56,600
Wait!

187
00:08:56,733 --> 00:08:58,733
Was that Dad shouting?

188
00:08:58,867 --> 00:08:59,700
Yes.

189
00:08:59,833 --> 00:09:01,800
And the other one's Uncle Noah!

190
00:09:01,933 --> 00:09:04,000
Let's go!

191
00:09:04,133 --> 00:09:05,133
Give me that!

192
00:09:05,267 --> 00:09:07,733
Uncle, stop!

193
00:09:07,867 --> 00:09:09,167
Stay out of this!

194
00:09:09,300 --> 00:09:11,200
Don't yell at my daughter!

195
00:09:11,333 --> 00:09:12,667
Shut up!

196
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:14,867
Go back to your wife!

197
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,767
You have no place
in this family anymore!

198
00:09:16,900 --> 00:09:17,767
And you?

199
00:09:17,900 --> 00:09:19,067
Are you even part
of this family?

200
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:20,533
You've got some nerve!

201
00:09:20,667 --> 00:09:22,133
You're not even married
to Felma yet!

202
00:09:22,267 --> 00:09:23,133
But the way you act,

203
00:09:23,267 --> 00:09:26,100
it's like you own her
and our children!

204
00:09:26,233 --> 00:09:27,467
They're not your family!

205
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:29,133
You bastard!

206
00:09:29,300 --> 00:09:30,867
Noah!

207
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:32,733
You saw he was already
in a wheelchair,

208
00:09:32,867 --> 00:09:34,233
and you still went after him?

209
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:46,600
Auntie Andrea, remember
what I said, okay?

210
00:09:46,733 --> 00:09:49,600
Once Grandpa says sorry,
please forgive him.

211
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:54,667
Have some coffee first, Jeff.

212
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:55,500
It's okay.

213
00:09:55,633 --> 00:09:58,367
Andrea is in a hurry.

214
00:09:58,500 --> 00:09:59,767
All right then.
Bye, Auntie Andrea.

215
00:09:59,900 --> 00:10:00,900
Bye.

216
00:10:01,067 --> 00:10:01,967
- Bye, Dad.
- Be safe.

217
00:10:02,100 --> 00:10:03,200
Bye, Tetay.

218
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:04,833
- Bye.
- Bye.

219
00:10:11,900 --> 00:10:12,533
Jeff?

220
00:10:39,567 --> 00:10:41,667
You know what?
You're being so extra.

221
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:43,100
Really feeling it, huh?

222
00:10:43,233 --> 00:10:44,867
- Bitter much?
- Seriously? Over that?

223
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:46,633
You don't have a boyfriend.
That's why!

224
00:10:46,767 --> 00:10:49,200
Let's go.

225
00:10:49,333 --> 00:10:51,267
You're so dramatic.

226
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:52,867
Are you still in high school?

227
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:54,767
Noah, come on!

228
00:10:54,900 --> 00:10:56,267
You're even defending
that cheater.

229
00:10:58,167 --> 00:11:00,733
Uncle Noah, let's go now.

230
00:11:00,867 --> 00:11:01,700
Uncle, please.

231
00:11:04,633 --> 00:11:06,733
Miss Felma, please excuse us.

232
00:11:06,867 --> 00:11:10,033
I'll treat Dad's wound.

233
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:11,433
Felma, I'm sorry.

234
00:11:12,967 --> 00:11:17,033
I didn't mean for Noah and me
to run into each other.

235
00:11:17,167 --> 00:11:19,367
Coleen, do Jeff and Andrea
know about this?

236
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:20,533
No, they don't.

237
00:11:20,667 --> 00:11:23,133
You betrayed us!

238
00:11:23,267 --> 00:11:25,667
You even conspired
with your mother!

239
00:11:25,800 --> 00:11:28,733
No wonder my private
investigator couldn't find them

240
00:11:28,867 --> 00:11:30,800
because you've been hiding them
all along!

241
00:11:30,933 --> 00:11:32,733
Me? I'm fine.

242
00:11:32,867 --> 00:11:33,933
I'm okay with being betrayed.

243
00:11:34,067 --> 00:11:35,800
Who am I anyway?

244
00:11:35,933 --> 00:11:37,600
But Jeff and Andrea...

245
00:11:37,733 --> 00:11:40,200
Coleen, I don't think
they deserve this!

246
00:11:40,333 --> 00:11:43,600
Dad and Jessica are
only here temporarily!

247
00:11:43,767 --> 00:11:46,433
I just really need to keep them
hidden from Hazel because...

248
00:11:46,567 --> 00:11:48,167
But still!

249
00:11:48,300 --> 00:11:50,500
You shouldn't have
brought them here!

250
00:11:50,633 --> 00:11:54,267
You conspired with Felma
to hide them from your siblings?

251
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:56,800
I have no intention
of telling Mom!

252
00:11:56,933 --> 00:11:58,433
She just happened to catch us!

253
00:12:00,533 --> 00:12:01,500
Coleen.

254
00:12:04,100 --> 00:12:05,300
Leave us for a moment.

255
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:24,300
When Manuel's wife stormed in,

256
00:12:24,433 --> 00:12:27,633
did you already know
that he was here?

257
00:12:27,767 --> 00:12:30,333
Were you already hiding him
then?

258
00:12:30,467 --> 00:12:32,067
No.

259
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:32,967
When did you find out?

260
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:39,100
When did you start conspiring
with Coleen?

261
00:12:39,233 --> 00:12:42,833
And when did you
start lying to me?

262
00:12:42,967 --> 00:12:44,633
I'm not lying to you!

263
00:12:44,767 --> 00:12:46,267
We're not together anymore!

264
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:49,033
I don't owe you
any explanations,

265
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:51,233
and you have no right
to yell at me!

266
00:12:58,467 --> 00:13:01,133
Dad, where's Jessica?

267
00:13:01,267 --> 00:13:03,567
She went to get a towel.

268
00:13:03,700 --> 00:13:05,233
Are you okay, Dad?

269
00:13:05,367 --> 00:13:06,400
I'm sorry, Coleen.

270
00:13:07,933 --> 00:13:11,133
I couldn't even defend
myself properly.

271
00:13:11,267 --> 00:13:13,267
It's embarrassing.

272
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:16,267
Dad, the fight
wasn't exactly fair.

273
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:20,267
Uncle Noah knew your condition,
but he still went for it anyway!

274
00:13:21,900 --> 00:13:25,100
You can't really blame him.

275
00:13:25,233 --> 00:13:26,800
Of course, he got jealous.

276
00:13:28,667 --> 00:13:30,633
Even I got jealous of Noah.

277
00:13:30,767 --> 00:13:34,367
I know I shouldn't,
and I don't have the right to.

278
00:13:34,500 --> 00:13:37,300
But I just couldn't help it.

279
00:13:37,433 --> 00:13:38,267
Dad...

280
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:42,633
I understand.

281
00:13:42,767 --> 00:13:45,333
I know you still love Mom.

282
00:13:45,467 --> 00:13:47,133
It's just...

283
00:13:47,267 --> 00:13:53,367
I'm not really sure if she
feels the same way about you.

284
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:56,033
But I do know that she
still cares about you.

285
00:13:58,433 --> 00:14:02,000
Dear, your mom doesn't
love me anymore.

286
00:14:02,133 --> 00:14:03,767
I know.

287
00:14:03,900 --> 00:14:06,167
I know that.

288
00:14:06,300 --> 00:14:07,633
Maybe...

289
00:14:07,767 --> 00:14:10,267
she just pities me because
of what is happening

290
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:12,467
with me and Jessica.

291
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:13,833
But you know what?

292
00:14:13,967 --> 00:14:15,500
I'm okay with that.

293
00:14:20,433 --> 00:14:21,300
Jessica?

294
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:27,000
Hey, are you okay?

295
00:14:27,133 --> 00:14:29,400
Coleen, I just realized

296
00:14:29,567 --> 00:14:33,067
that Sir Noah might tell Andrea
and Jeffrey.

297
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:44,167
You don't owe me an explanation.

298
00:14:44,833 --> 00:14:46,733
But seriously, Felma?

299
00:14:46,867 --> 00:14:49,400
This is where you're hiding
your ex?

300
00:14:49,533 --> 00:14:51,933
Even though you know Jeffrey
and Andrea would be furious?

301
00:14:52,067 --> 00:14:54,000
You don't know what's going on.

302
00:14:54,133 --> 00:14:56,700
And don't you dare
say anything to them.

303
00:14:56,833 --> 00:14:58,200
Don't speak for me.

304
00:14:58,333 --> 00:14:59,933
This is a family matter.

305
00:15:00,067 --> 00:15:01,700
You're not part of this!

306
00:15:01,867 --> 00:15:04,433
So that's really
how you see me, huh?

307
00:15:04,567 --> 00:15:06,633
An outsider in your family.

308
00:15:06,767 --> 00:15:08,933
And here I was, still hoping
we'd get back together.

309
00:15:11,300 --> 00:15:14,067
I thought we could make
this family whole.

310
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:16,167
But it turns out there's nothing
left for me to hope for

311
00:15:16,300 --> 00:15:19,067
because the man who cheated
on you is back.

312
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:24,100
Manuel has nothing to do
with why we didn't work out.

313
00:15:24,233 --> 00:15:25,967
Felma, are you really
still going to lie to me?

314
00:15:28,567 --> 00:15:30,533
It's so obvious!

315
00:15:30,667 --> 00:15:31,967
Even with my eyes closed,

316
00:15:32,100 --> 00:15:34,133
I can see that your whole world
still revolves

317
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:37,733
around that stupid man
who betrayed you!

318
00:15:37,867 --> 00:15:39,867
It wasn't just Manuel
who got hurt.

319
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:40,933
I did too.

320
00:15:41,067 --> 00:15:43,567
But did you ever notice me?

321
00:15:43,700 --> 00:15:45,433
No!

322
00:15:45,567 --> 00:15:48,433
Because all your attention
was on him!

323
00:15:48,567 --> 00:15:54,533
Noah, if I reverse
the situation,

324
00:15:56,200 --> 00:16:01,567
let's say you're the one in the
wheelchair and Manuel barges in,

325
00:16:01,700 --> 00:16:03,167
I will go to you!

326
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:04,700
And now you're trying
to justify it?

327
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:10,633
Please, just admit it.

328
00:16:10,767 --> 00:16:12,000
You still love Manuel.

329
00:16:15,467 --> 00:16:18,067
I give up.

330
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:19,067
I'm getting hurt too much

331
00:16:19,200 --> 00:16:21,900
by everything you're
doing to me.

332
00:16:22,033 --> 00:16:23,967
No matter what I do...

333
00:16:24,100 --> 00:16:29,200
Even if I begged you right now,
it wouldn't change anything.

334
00:16:29,333 --> 00:16:30,733
Because in the end,
you'll still choose that demon

335
00:16:30,867 --> 00:16:31,967
who hurt you.

336
00:16:32,100 --> 00:16:36,267
I'm not choosing
either you or Manuel.

337
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:37,700
No one.

338
00:16:37,833 --> 00:16:38,767
Really? No one?

339
00:17:21,867 --> 00:17:24,100
What exactly is missing?

340
00:17:24,233 --> 00:17:26,433
The monthly sales report
from our five branches.

341
00:17:26,567 --> 00:17:28,467
I can't find it.

342
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:29,500
No soft copy?

343
00:17:31,567 --> 00:17:32,467
There is.

344
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:34,467
But what I need
is the manual computation.

345
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:36,600
That's what I have
to cross-check.

346
00:17:36,733 --> 00:17:38,500
Oh no.

347
00:17:38,633 --> 00:17:39,567
Five branches?

348
00:17:39,700 --> 00:17:40,133
That's a lot.

349
00:17:43,267 --> 00:17:46,000
So, that means I have to do
everything manually now.

350
00:17:46,133 --> 00:17:48,633
I spent days working
on that, Jeff.

351
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:51,600
And now I have to dig
through all the receipts

352
00:17:51,733 --> 00:17:54,267
from Konsumo Mart again.

353
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:56,833
Maybe you left it with Angge.

354
00:17:56,967 --> 00:17:58,300
No, Jeff. I had it.

355
00:17:58,433 --> 00:17:59,567
It was with me.

356
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:00,833
It should be here.

357
00:18:00,967 --> 00:18:02,600
It could have fallen somewhere.

358
00:18:04,667 --> 00:18:06,733
Then you go look for it.

359
00:18:06,867 --> 00:18:09,433
If it fell,
then it wouldn't be here.

360
00:18:09,567 --> 00:18:11,467
It was here.

361
00:18:11,600 --> 00:18:12,400
So annoying!

362
00:18:17,833 --> 00:18:18,800
Bro, I found her.

363
00:18:21,833 --> 00:18:25,400
That's just more for your
collection of babes.

364
00:18:25,533 --> 00:18:29,033
Bro, is that babe number 5?

365
00:18:29,167 --> 00:18:31,333
This one is babe number 1.

366
00:18:31,467 --> 00:18:32,467
Babe number 1?

367
00:18:32,600 --> 00:18:35,233
I thought that was Bea?

368
00:18:35,367 --> 00:18:38,433
Didn't you upgrade her

369
00:18:38,567 --> 00:18:41,767
from babe number 3
to babe number 1?

370
00:18:41,900 --> 00:18:43,733
She's old news.

371
00:18:43,867 --> 00:18:46,200
She's been downgraded
to babe number 2.

372
00:18:46,333 --> 00:18:51,500
What's up with that
Andrea Cruz anyway?

373
00:18:51,633 --> 00:18:54,733
She's different
from my usual type.

374
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:56,433
Simple.

375
00:18:56,567 --> 00:18:57,500
Looks decent.

376
00:19:12,233 --> 00:19:13,900
Wait. Are you stalking her?

377
00:19:14,033 --> 00:19:15,700
Bro, that's new.

378
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:18,433
You're the one being
chased by the babes.

379
00:19:18,567 --> 00:19:21,600
Feels like
the roles are reversed.

380
00:19:21,733 --> 00:19:23,567
Just to mix things up.

381
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:25,833
I'm tired of girls
chasing after me.

382
00:19:25,967 --> 00:19:27,433
Who are you kidding?

383
00:19:27,567 --> 00:19:29,533
I would bet my car on it.

384
00:19:29,700 --> 00:19:32,167
You'll just make her
the flavor of the month.

385
00:19:32,300 --> 00:19:33,533
- So?
- Game!

386
00:19:33,667 --> 00:19:34,200
Cheers!

387
00:19:34,333 --> 00:19:36,300
All right.

388
00:19:36,433 --> 00:19:37,067
Come in.

389
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:45,200
Is your wound okay now?

390
00:19:47,700 --> 00:19:50,500
I was actually talking to Abel.

391
00:19:50,633 --> 00:19:52,300
He said he found an apartment.

392
00:19:52,433 --> 00:19:55,100
But it's still three more
days before we can move in

393
00:19:55,233 --> 00:19:58,167
because there are still some
things that need fixing.

394
00:19:58,300 --> 00:20:02,433
I was thinking maybe we could
just stay in a hotel for now.

395
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:04,533
No, don't.

396
00:20:04,667 --> 00:20:06,867
You and Jessica are already
worried about money,

397
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:08,367
and you want to spend more?

398
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:11,267
No, it's just a cheap one.

399
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:14,433
Instead of spending it
on a hotel,

400
00:20:14,567 --> 00:20:18,433
why don't you use the money
to buy your new stuff?

401
00:20:18,567 --> 00:20:21,833
You won't be able to get
your stuff there

402
00:20:21,967 --> 00:20:23,967
at the Airbnb, right?

403
00:20:24,100 --> 00:20:27,933
Yes, but what about
Jeffrey and Andrea?

404
00:20:28,067 --> 00:20:31,567
Noah won't tell them.

405
00:20:31,700 --> 00:20:32,833
Are you sure?

406
00:20:32,967 --> 00:20:34,500
He's really angry.

407
00:20:34,633 --> 00:20:37,100
I'm sure he'll tell our kids.

408
00:20:37,267 --> 00:20:38,233
He's not like that.

409
00:20:40,467 --> 00:20:44,500
If I tell Noah that I'll handle
my own problems,

410
00:20:44,633 --> 00:20:46,100
he won't interfere.

411
00:20:49,633 --> 00:20:52,300
I've wronged you so many times.

412
00:20:52,433 --> 00:20:56,800
I might end up messing things up
with you and Noah.

413
00:20:56,933 --> 00:20:59,233
Didn't Coleen tell you?

414
00:20:59,367 --> 00:21:03,000
Noah and I were already
separated before you came.

415
00:21:03,133 --> 00:21:04,800
Oh, really?

416
00:21:04,933 --> 00:21:07,600
I thought you were
about to get married?

417
00:21:07,733 --> 00:21:10,233
I can't love anymore.

418
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:14,367
Perhaps marriage
or relationships...

419
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:17,833
just aren't meant for me.

420
00:21:17,967 --> 00:21:22,267
There's only one man I see
walking me down the aisle.

421
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:23,433
It's you.

422
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:31,767
But we both know
that won't happen.

423
00:21:31,900 --> 00:21:32,867
It's not possible anymore.

424
00:21:36,067 --> 00:21:38,300
<i>Once I've saved enough,
I'll come home right away.</i>

425
00:21:38,433 --> 00:21:41,467
<i> Think about Andrea's surgery.</i>

426
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:42,633
<i> When that happens,</i>

427
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:44,800
<i>your dad won't have
to leave anymore.</i>

428
00:21:44,933 --> 00:21:46,433
We won't be apart anymore.

429
00:21:46,567 --> 00:21:47,833
<i> I promise.</i>

430
00:21:47,967 --> 00:21:48,867
<i> Hazel, what happened?</i>

431
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:50,900
<i>You were forcing me to kiss you.</i>

432
00:21:51,033 --> 00:21:51,967
<i> Hazel, please forgive me.</i>

433
00:21:52,100 --> 00:21:54,600
<i>- But it already happened.
- I need to go.</i>

434
00:21:54,733 --> 00:21:57,767
<i>Under the laws of the Republic
of the Philippines,</i>

435
00:21:57,900 --> 00:22:01,733
<i>Manuel Cruz, if you freely
and voluntarily consent</i>

436
00:22:01,867 --> 00:22:05,533
<i>to be united in marriage
to Hazel Capistrano...</i>

437
00:22:10,467 --> 00:22:11,167
<i> I do.</i>

438
00:22:15,900 --> 00:22:18,367
Forgive me for everything
I've done to you.

439
00:22:21,333 --> 00:22:22,600
I'm sorry, Felma.

440
00:23:02,533 --> 00:23:07,567
Felma, even though
you don't believe in marriage,

441
00:23:07,700 --> 00:23:09,233
didn't I promise to marry you?

442
00:23:11,067 --> 00:23:13,000
And I promised you
back then that...

443
00:23:15,333 --> 00:23:17,900
I'd give you a happy family,
but...

444
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:24,533
I wasn't able to do it.

445
00:23:27,500 --> 00:23:29,767
I wasn't able to do it.
I failed you.

446
00:23:34,233 --> 00:23:39,133
I ruined your life
and our children's too.

447
00:23:39,267 --> 00:23:44,767
I admit, Manuel,
the pain is still there.

448
00:23:44,900 --> 00:23:49,800
It comes out whenever I remember
how hard it was for our kids

449
00:23:49,933 --> 00:23:52,533
when you left us.

450
00:23:52,667 --> 00:23:54,667
But that's over now.

451
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:57,367
It's not right for me to hold on
to anger anymore.

452
00:24:00,533 --> 00:24:02,267
I forgive you.

453
00:24:07,433 --> 00:24:10,067
Thank you so much, Felma.

454
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:16,233
Even if we weren't meant to be,
we were friends, weren't we?

455
00:24:16,367 --> 00:24:17,767
We can try...

456
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:22,767
to bring that back.

457
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:27,700
Felma, I promise you,
I won't break your trust again.

458
00:24:27,833 --> 00:24:30,667
Even if it's just as friends.

459
00:24:32,033 --> 00:24:33,000
I promise.

460
00:24:44,667 --> 00:24:46,767
I'm sure that flirt Felma knows

461
00:24:47,400 --> 00:24:48,533
where my husband
and daughter are.

462
00:24:48,667 --> 00:24:50,267
She's hiding them somewhere.

463
00:24:50,400 --> 00:24:52,300
So, what's your plan?

464
00:24:52,433 --> 00:24:53,433
<i> You know what?</i>

465
00:24:53,567 --> 00:24:57,567
I need someone to infiltrate
Felma's Meat Products,

466
00:24:57,700 --> 00:25:01,900
to gain Felma's trust,
and get information.

467
00:25:02,067 --> 00:25:05,700
That's why I called
my sister, Hilda.

468
00:25:05,833 --> 00:25:06,867
<i> Hilda?</i>

469
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:08,933
She's dumb.

470
00:25:09,067 --> 00:25:12,667
We need someone who actually
knows how to scheme.

471
00:25:12,800 --> 00:25:15,033
Well, she's the only one
available.

472
00:25:15,167 --> 00:25:17,800
Don't worry,
I'll just train her.

473
00:25:17,933 --> 00:25:19,300
You have a choice.

474
00:25:19,433 --> 00:25:22,100
You have me.

475
00:25:22,233 --> 00:25:22,967
What do you mean?

476
00:25:26,467 --> 00:25:27,433
Wait.

477
00:25:30,467 --> 00:25:32,833
Alice! Hey!

478
00:25:32,967 --> 00:25:33,867
When did you...

479
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:35,033
Wait, I'll end the call.

480
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:36,533
Come on!

481
00:25:36,667 --> 00:25:37,700
You're here!

482
00:25:37,833 --> 00:25:38,667
Since when?

483
00:25:38,800 --> 00:25:39,433
What happened?

484
00:25:39,567 --> 00:25:42,000
Why didn't you tell me?

485
00:25:42,133 --> 00:25:43,933
Well...

486
00:25:44,067 --> 00:25:45,100
What's the plan?

487
00:25:50,733 --> 00:25:51,767
Ma'am Andrea.

488
00:25:51,900 --> 00:25:54,767
Didn't I tell you
not to bother me right now?

489
00:25:54,900 --> 00:25:57,833
Your staff did tell me,
but I insisted.

490
00:25:57,967 --> 00:25:58,733
I'm Joel Santiago.

491
00:25:58,867 --> 00:26:00,300
Why are you packing your things?

492
00:26:00,433 --> 00:26:02,467
- I'm leaving.
- Resigning?

493
00:26:02,600 --> 00:26:04,400
Yes.

494
00:26:04,533 --> 00:26:05,567
Okay.

495
00:26:05,700 --> 00:26:07,633
Is it that easy for you
to just let me go like that?

496
00:26:07,767 --> 00:26:09,933
What do you want me to do?

497
00:26:10,100 --> 00:26:11,133
Stop you?

498
00:26:11,267 --> 00:26:12,333
Yes.

499
00:26:12,467 --> 00:26:14,300
Jeff and I have been noticing
a lot about you, Mom.

500
00:26:14,433 --> 00:26:16,400
You're hiding something from us.

501
00:26:16,533 --> 00:26:18,133
And now, Uncle Noah is leaving

502
00:26:18,267 --> 00:26:20,300
because he said you're making
a fool out of him!

503
00:26:20,433 --> 00:26:22,433
Please, enough with the secrets!

504
00:26:22,567 --> 00:26:23,467
You're right.

505
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:25,000
I've been hiding Manuel.

506
00:26:25,133 --> 00:26:27,267
- Andrea!
- Andrea, stop it, please!

507
00:26:27,400 --> 00:26:29,100
- Andrea!
- Let go of me!

508
00:26:29,233 --> 00:26:29,700
Andrea!

509
00:26:29,833 --> 00:26:30,700
Ma'am Andrea!

510
00:26:30,833 --> 00:26:31,800
Andrea!
